AN ACT
To repeal sections 59.319 and 60.590, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof two new sections relating
to land surveying.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Sections 59.319 and 60.590, RSMo, are repealed
2 and two new sections enacted in lieu thereof, to be known as
3 sections 59.319 and 60.590, to read as follows:
1 59.319. 1. A user fee of [four] six dollars shall be
2 charged and collected by every recorder in this state, over
3 and above any other fees required by law, as a condition
4 precedent to the recording of any instrument. The state
5 portion of the fee shall be forwarded monthly by each
6 recorder of deeds to the state director of revenue, and the
7 fees so forwarded shall be deposited by the director in the
8 state treasury. [Two] Three dollars of such fee shall be
9 retained by the recorder and deposited in a recorder's fund
10 and not in county general revenue for record storage,
11 microfilming, and preservation, including anything
12 necessarily pertaining thereto. The recorder's funds shall
13 be kept in a special fund by the treasurer and shall be
14 budgeted and expended at the direction of the recorder and
15 shall not be used to substitute for or subsidize any
16 allocation of general revenue for the operation of the
EXPLANATION-Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in this bill is not enacted
and is intended to be omitted in the law.

